From fae627f0be885f77d211b32e40c60907431f0dbb Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Mon, 11 May 2026 19:27:35 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Launch DedTxt v0.5.0

Current state of the app for initial launch:

- Dead simple plain-text editor backed by a single <textarea>. Same
  code drives every platform: Electron on macOS / Windows / Linux,
  a PWA, and Capacitor on iOS / Android.

- src/platform/{electron,web,capacitor}.js wraps the I/O for each
  runtime behind a uniform interface; renderer.js is
  platform-agnostic and picks the right module at startup.

- Web build via scripts/build-web.js produces dist-web/ with a
  landing page (auto-detected download buttons + GitHub Releases
  lookup) at /, and the installable PWA at /app/.

- Dark theme by default with a per-surface toggle; choice persisted
  in localStorage under 'dedtxt-theme' and shared between landing
  and PWA.

- Icon: bone-white skull with pink slice displacement + chromatic
  aberration on the 'dedtxt' wordmark, sourced from
  build/icon.svg. npm run gen:icons rebuilds the .icns / .ico /
  .png and PWA icon set. npm run gen:social produces a 1280x640
  social preview at build/social-preview.png.

- electron-builder configured for .dmg + .zip (mac, x64 + arm64),
  NSIS + portable .exe (win, x64 + arm64), and AppImage + .deb +
  .rpm (linux). File associations for txt/md/log/json/csv/ini/
  yml/yaml/xml.

- Android Capacitor project committed (com.cportka.dedtxt) with
  intent-filters for ACTION_VIEW / EDIT / SEND on text/* MIME
  types. iOS project is scaffolded on demand from macOS.

- GitHub Actions builds desktop installers + unsigned APK +
  simulator-only iOS .app on every push, attaches them all to a
  GitHub Release on v* tags, and redeploys the static site to the
  gh-pages branch automatically. Site lives at
  https://cportka.github.io/dedtxt/.

- README hero image renders the SVG icon at the top of the file.
